A face-off looms in the Elgeyo Marakwet county assembly as MCAs demand cancellation of fresh recruitment of employees.On Thursday last week, MCAs, led by Kapyego s Benson Kiptire, accused speaker Albert Kochei of spearheading fresh recruitment against recommendations to freeze hiring to lower the wage bill.Kiptire said they agreed with the speaker in a Kamukunji to stop further recruitment. Interviews for recently advertised jobs were ongoing as the MCAs addressed the press on Friday.